        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 8:48PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 846 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from 11 miles northeast of
Richfield to 4 miles south of Wilburton to 4 miles south of Keyes to
5 miles southeast of Felt to Clayton. Movement was south at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Guymon, Dalhart, Stratford, Hartley, Cactus, Sunray, Hooker,
Goodwell, Tyrone, Texline, Optima, Hardesty, Hough, Adams, Griggs,
Eva, Ware, Baker, Conlen, and Texhoma.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

These storms may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
